HANTAVIRUS PULMONARY SYNDROME - USA: UPDATE JUNE 22
***************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Hantavirus pulmonary syndrome - Canada: update Jan 19 980121005100
Hantavirus pulmonary syndrome - USA: Update Jan 14 980118155105
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 1998 12:14:00 -0400
From: Joni Young <gzc8@cdc.gov>

As of June 22, 1998, the Centers for Disease Control & Prevention has
confirmed a total of 185 cases of Hantavirus Pulmonary Syndrome (HPS) in 29
states. Four cases with onset in 1998 have been confirmed so far.
Updated Statistics:
--------------------------
N=185
81 (44%) died
Male: 113 (61%)
White: 140 (76%)
American Indian: 39 (21%)
Black: 5
Asian: 1
Hispanic: 21 (11%)
Mean Age: 37 [11-69
--
Joni Young
CDC, Special Pathogens Branch
1600 Clifton Rd. NE, MS A-26
Atlanta, GA 30333
email: gzc8@cdc.gov
